cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a novel FCN-ConvLSTM model for predicting human driver attention from monocular dash camera videos. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the training paradigm and proposes a solution to improve the performance of the model. 
3. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper introduces the concept of using human gaze to determine the sampling weights for the learning frames. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a machine learning model for predicting human driver attention. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper discusses the application of the proposed model in driving-related tasks, which can be relevant to robotics.
